        aria-labelledby="title-accessibility-statement">

        <h1
            id="title-accessibility-statement"
            class="heading-alpha">
            {{content.title.accessibility}}
        </h1>

    </header>

    <section class="l-content__body">

        <p class="c-lede">
            This site is committed to providing an experience that functions for the widest possible audience, regardless of technology or ability.
        </p>
        <p>
            It strives to conform to level <a rel="external noopener" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/">AA compliance for the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (<abbr title="Web Content Accessibility Guidelines">WCAG</abbr>) 2.0</a>. These are guidelines that explain how to make web content easier to use for people with disabilities.
        </p>
        <p>
            The code powering this site is <a href="https://www.w3.org/standards/">standards-compliant <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup Language">HTML</abbr>, <abbr title="Cascading Style Sheets">CSS</abbr>, and JavaScript</a>. Any person using a past, present, or future browser that honors these standards should be capable of navigating this site.
        </p>
        <p>
            In addition to being tested on modern browsers, both <a rel="external noopener" href="http://www.apple.com/accessibility/osx/voiceover/">mac&#8202;OS Voice&#8202;Over</a> and <a rel="external noopener" href="http://www.nvaccess.org/">NV Access&rsquo;s <abbr title="NonVisual Desktop Access">NVDA</abbr></a> have been used to test this site for ease of use with a screen reader. It has also been audited using <a rel="external noopener" href="http://wave.webaim.org/about">WebAIM&rsquo;s <abbr title="Web Accessibility Evaluation Tool">WAVE</a>, as well as the <a rel="external noopener" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/accessibility-developer-t/fpkknkljclfencbdbgkenhalefipecmb">Chrome</a>, and <a rel="external noopener" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/axe/lhdoppojpmngadmnindnejefpokejbdd"><abbr title="Accessibility Engine">aXe</abbr></a> developer testing tool extensions.
        </p>
        <p id="accessibility-issues" class="c-accessibility-issues">
            Issues with this site&rsquo;s accessibility can be submitted as a <a rel="external noopener" href="https://github.com/ericwbailey/ericwbailey.design/issues">Git&#8202;Hub issue</a>, or by <a data-message-subject="Accessibility issue" rel="external noopener" href="mailto:&#101;&#114;&#105;&#099;&#046;&#119;&#046;&#098;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#101;&#121;☛REMOVE-THIS☚&#064;&#103;&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;?subject=&#065;&#099;&#099;&#101;&#115;&#115;&#105;&#098;&#105;&#108;&#105;&#116;&#121;&#032;&#105;&#115;&#115;&#117;&#101;">emailing me directly</a>. I take these issues very seriously and will try to remedy the problem as quickly as time allows. A list of <a rel="external noopener" href="https://github.com/ericwbailey/ericwbailey.design/wiki/Accessibility-Testing-Warnings-and-Errors">known reported issues</a> is also available.
        </p>
        <p>
            Although I cannot guarantee that all content linked to, or embedded on this site is fully accessible, I try to choose sites and services that embrace <a rel="external noopener" href="http://inclusivedesignprinciples.org/">Inclusive Design principles</a>.
        </p>

    </section>

</main>

